HEADWORD: Scaphocephaly
<hw>Scaph`o*ceph"a*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ska`fh</grk> a boat + <grk>kefalh`</grk> head.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A deformed condition of the skull, in which the
vault is narrow, elongated, and more or less boat-shaped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scaphocerite</ent>⟦br⟧
